                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At 6: 53 a. m. (<gloss target="#t_EDT1">EDT</gloss>) on July 1 a teletype
                    conference was held with <gloss target="#t_HQ1">HQ</gloss>, <gloss
                        target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss> in Tokyo by military officials in Washington
                    along with representatives of the Department of State and other agencies (<gloss
                        target="#t_DA1">DA</gloss> TT–3445). <gloss target="#t_G21">G–2</gloss> in
                    Tokyo reported that the North Koreans threatened Suwon and that the members of
                    the disorganized <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Government had moved to
                    Taejon. (<hi rend="italic">Korean Conflict</hi>)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
